# DOCUMENTATION

## Synopsis

Here I aim to completely analyze the process of maintaining and customizing a jekyll, github-powered site, through my own experiences and mistakes so that anyone can find a plethora of tips and important stuff I couldn't find in one place but rather scattered around the internet. It will include:
 - Detailed analysis of the site files
 - The connection between them and how to modify each one in corellation with the others
 - The commands and steps needed to get it running


Throughout this file I will include references to many of my posts in which I will describe specific functions and programms to the greatest (in my powers) extent. When I finish writing these *specific* articles (they will have a rather narrow focus point) I will convert this file to a full-sized article for better documentation and reading experience. Till then: have fun :P.

## Site Organization
The main files you need to pay attention to when creating and tailoring your site to your needs are basically three:
- The 'index.html' file
- The 'config.yml' file

### The index.html
Navigating through this file should be plain as day even for someone that doesn't normally work with html (such as me). When I saw [augustohp's website](https://augustohp.github.com) I was fascinated by its simplicity and elegance so I immediately decided that the initial slate I would build my website on would be his. From then I made quite some improvements, *at least from my point of view*, just to bring the site closer to my taste of balance and minimalism. I had to start from somewhere just to gain an understanding of how the website works ( I didn't have the slightest idea about it ) so I immediately started reading every file there to try and see the relations between each one of them. By tweaking the files I came to the first realization: ** index.html is exactly what its name suggest ** . Of course it's silly reading that now, you must be like *wow, he is a total idiot*, however, it didn't seem so obvious for me then. Take a moment to compare [my index file](chatziiola/chatziiola.github.io/index.html)

